## Integration: Prompts ↔ Memory (Entity Variables)

> [!IMPORTANT]
> All prompts used by the Memory System must be **written in and/or imported from the Prompt Manager**. Entity fields and pipeline context are injected as variables.

### The Bridge: Entity Fields as Prompt Variables

When you define an entity type with custom fields, those fields become available as **prompt variables** in any prompt that processes that entity:

```
Entity Type: "contact"
├── name: "John Doe"            →  {{entity.name}}
├── stage: "qualified"          →  {{entity.stage}}  
├── company: "Acme Corp"        →  {{entity.company}}
├── source: "inbound"           →  {{entity.source}}
└── custom_field: "premium"     →  {{entity.custom_field}}
```

In the Prompt Editor, writing a memory generation prompt looks like:

```markdown
You are an AI memory system analyzing interactions for {{entity.name}} 
({{entity.type}} — {{entity.stage}}).

This entity belongs to {{entity.company}}, sourced via {{entity.source}}.

Based on {{interaction_count}} interactions on {{date}}, write a concise 
factual memory record.

{{#if prior_context}}
PRIOR CONTEXT (established facts, do NOT repeat):
{{prior_context}}
{{/if}}

RAW INTERACTIONS:
{{raw_interactions}}

EXTRACTED SIGNALS:
{{ner_signals}}
```

**This means**: the user writes their memory system prompts using the same editor, same variable system, same versioning as their agent identity prompts. The difference is only in *where the variables come from* at render time.

### Variable Resolution at Runtime

```mermaid
graph LR
    subgraph "Variable Sources"
        ENT["Entity Fields<br/>{{entity.*}}"]
        PIPE["Pipeline Context<br/>{{date}}, {{interaction_count}}"]
        DATA["Processed Data<br/>{{raw_interactions}}, {{ner_signals}}"]
        USER["User-defined<br/>{{custom_var}}"]
    end

    subgraph "Prompt Manager"
        RENDER["Render Engine"]
        PROMPT["Versioned Prompt<br/>with {{variables}}"]
    end

    subgraph "Memory Pipeline"
        TASK["memory_tasks.py"]
        RESULT["Compiled prompt<br/>→ LLM call"]
    end

    ENT --> RENDER
    PIPE --> RENDER
    DATA --> RENDER
    USER --> RENDER
    PROMPT --> RENDER
    RENDER --> RESULT
    TASK -->|"provides context"| RENDER
```

### What This Unlocks

| Capability | Description |
|---|---|
| **"Chat with an entity field"** | Write `{{entity.stage}}` in a prompt and the pipeline resolves it from the entity's actual data |
| **Prompt versioning for ML** | A/B test memory generation prompts by switching Git branches |
| **Unified editing** | One editor (Prompt Manager) for all prompts — agent identity AND memory pipeline |
| **Entity-aware prompts** | Different prompts per entity type, with type-specific fields injected |
| **Reuse** | A prompt crafted for the pipeline can also be rendered via API for external use |

