## MasterAgent AI Assistant

> [!IMPORTANT]
> Since the user already configures their own LLM API keys, the platform should use those keys to power an **AI assistant that helps the user configure the platform itself**.

### Concept

A **chat bubble / sidebar** accessible from anywhere in the app. The user talks to "MasterAgent" — an AI persona that understands the platform's configuration model and can execute changes through tool calling.

```
┌──────────────────────────────────────┐
│ 🤖 MasterAgent                    ─ │
│                                      │
│ You: "I'm setting up a CRM          │
│ integration. I need to track         │
│ contacts with fields: name,          │
│ company, deal_stage, and source.     │
│ Set up daily memory generation       │
│ with strict PII filtering."          │
│                                      │
│ MasterAgent: "I'll set that up.      │
│ Here's what I'm doing:               │
│                                      │
│ ✅ Created entity type 'contact'     │
│    with subtypes: lead, client       │
│ ✅ Added custom fields: company,     │
│    deal_stage, source                │
│ ✅ Enabled PII scrubbing             │
│ ✅ Set generation schedule: 02:00    │
│ ✅ Created webhook source 'CRM'      │
│                                      │
│ Want me to also create a memory      │
│ generation prompt optimized for      │
│ CRM interactions?"                   │
│                                      │
│ [Type a message...]            Send  │
└──────────────────────────────────────┘
```

### How It Works

1. **Uses the user's own LLM** — routes through the configured LLM provider (same infrastructure as the memory pipeline)
2. **Tool calling / function calling** — MasterAgent has tools that map to platform APIs:

```
Available Tools:
├── Prompts
│   ├── create_prompt(name, description)
│   ├── add_section(prompt_id, name, content)
│   ├── add_variable(prompt_id, name, type, default)
│   └── update_section(prompt_id, section, content)
│
├── Memory
│   ├── create_entity_type(name, icon, description)
│   ├── add_entity_subtype(type_id, name)
│   ├── add_entity_field(type, field_name, field_type)
│   ├── update_pipeline_config(tab, settings)
│   ├── assign_llm_task(task_type, provider_id, model)
│   └── create_webhook_source(name, system, config)
│
├── Settings
│   ├── update_memory_settings(key, value)
│   ├── add_llm_provider(name, provider, api_key)
│   └── update_llm_provider(id, settings)
│
└── Tools (future)
    ├── register_mcp_server(url, name)
    └── list_available_tools()
```

3. **Context-aware** — MasterAgent knows the current page/tab the user is on and can offer contextual help
4. **Reads current state** — before making changes, it reads the current configuration to avoid duplicates and suggest improvements

### What The User Can Do

| User says | MasterAgent does |
|---|---|
| *"I'm hooking up Intercom. Set up webhook with PII filtering"* | Creates webhook source, enables PII, creates entity type if needed |
| *"Write me a memory generation prompt that's good for sales conversations"* | Creates a prompt in the Prompt Manager with optimized sections and variables |
| *"Change NER to use GPT-4o instead of GLiNER"* | Updates the entity_extraction LLM config |
| *"Show me what my pipeline looks like right now"* | Reads all configs and presents a summary |
| *"I want more aggressive insight generation — check every 5 memories"* | Updates compaction_threshold to 5 |
| *"Add a 'priority' field to contacts"* | Adds field to entity type config metadata_field_map |

### Implementation Notes

- The MasterAgent persona prompt itself would be a **Prompt Manager entry** (dogfooding Layer 1)
- The tool definitions are essentially an **MCP server** that wraps the platform's own REST API (dogfooding Layer 3)
- The chat UI could reuse patterns from the entity workspace chat (already built in `memory/workspace.py`)
- LLM calls route through the existing `call_llm()` infrastructure with the user's configured provider

